{"title":"Park Tool Rolls Out Professional Chain Tool, New Floor Pump & Updated Bottle Opener","link":"https://bikerumor.com/park-tool-ct-15-chain-tool-bo-6-bottle-opener/","date":1720034538000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-chain-breaking.jpeg\" width=\"900\" height=\"780\" alt=\"(Photos/Park Tool)\" /></p>\n<p>Bicycle tool giant, <a href=\"https://www.parktool.com/en-us/\" target=\"_blank\">Park Tool</a> is releasing updates to some popular tools in your shop. The new <a href=\"https://www.parktool.com/en-us/product/professional-chain-tool-ct-15?category=New+Products\" target=\"_blank\">CT-15</a> Professional Chain Tool, the <a href=\"https://www.parktool.com/en-us/product/home-mechanic-floor-pump-pfp-10?category=New+Products\" target=\"_blank\">PFP-10</a> Home Mechanic Floor Pump, and the <a href=\"https://www.parktool.com/en-us/product/bottle-opener-bo-6?category=New+Products\" target=\"_blank\">BO-6</a> Bottle Opener. Let’s get to the meat of this launch.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>CT-15 Professional Chain Tool</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opene.-CT-15-profilejpeg-e1720031314811.jpeg\"><img width=\"900\" height=\"654\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opene.-CT-15-profilejpeg-e1720031314811.jpeg\" alt=\"Park Tools Chain Breaker, Floor Pump and Bottle Opene. CT-15 profilejpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opene.-CT-15-profilejpeg-e1720031314811.jpeg 900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opene.-CT-15-profilejpeg-e1720031314811-297x216.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opene.-CT-15-profilejpeg-e1720031314811-120x87.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opene.-CT-15-profilejpeg-e1720031314811-768x558.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Park Tool)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new CT-15 is exactly what it says it is, a professional-grade chain tool capable of pushing chain pins in and out of any chain. That means everything from the beefy single-speed, half-link chains to the latest 13-speed systems. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-chain-breaking.jpeg\"><img width=\"900\" height=\"780\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-chain-breaking.jpeg\" alt=\"Park Tools Chain Breaker, Floor Pump and Bottle Opener CT-15 chain breaking\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-chain-breaking.jpeg 900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-chain-breaking-297x257.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-chain-breaking-120x104.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-chain-breaking-768x666.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Park Tool)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-storage.jpeg\"><img width=\"900\" height=\"780\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-storage.jpeg\" alt=\"Park Tools Chain Breaker, Floor Pump and Bottle Opener CT-15 storage\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-storage.jpeg 900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-storage-297x257.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-storage-120x104.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-CT-15-storage-768x666.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The magic lies in the unique floating shelf. It ensures that every chain is securely fixtured and centered during use.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another cool feature is that the ergonomic handle stores spare driving pins as well as a peening anvil for peening Campy 11, 12, and 13-speed chains. It’s built for daily use and is fully rebuildable.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>CT-15 Retail and Features</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $148</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Compatible with single-speed bicycle chains including 1/8”, 3/16” and half-link</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Compatible with all 5 to 13-speed derailleur chains, including SRAM 12-speed Flattop, SRAM 12-speed T-Type, Shimano 12-speed XTR, and Campagnolo 13-speed Ekar.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Includes removable anvil for peening Campagnolo 11 to 13-speed chains</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Includes two spare driving pins (part #2987)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>PFP-Home Mechanic Floor Pump</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s nothing like a good, reliable floor pump in a well-stocked home shop. Park Tool says that this new pump is equally at home in the garage, workshop, or trailhead. It comes equipped with a long hose, extra-large foot pads, and a giant easy-to-read gauge. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-Long-hose.jpeg\"><img width=\"600\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-Long-hose.jpeg\" alt=\"Park Tools Chain Breaker, Floor Pump and Bottle Opener Long hose\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-Long-hose.jpeg 600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-Long-hose-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-Long-hose-120x120.jpeg 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-Big-dial.jpeg\"><img width=\"600\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-Big-dial.jpeg\" alt=\"Park Tools Chain Breaker, Floor Pump and Bottle Opener Big dial\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-Big-dial.jpeg 600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-Big-dial-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-Big-dial-120x120.jpeg 120w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Lastly, the locking universal head is compatible with both Presta and Schrader valves. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>PFP Retail and Features</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $50</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Compatible with Presta and Schrader valves without switching internal parts</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Maximum pressure: 160 PSI (11 bar)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated pressure gauge and universal head (Presta, Schrader, Dunlop)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>BO-6 Bottle Opener</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-profile-e1720031742525.jpeg\"><img width=\"900\" height=\"426\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-profile-e1720031742525.jpeg\" alt=\"Park Tools Chain Breaker, Floor Pump and Bottle Opener BO-6 profile\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-profile-e1720031742525.jpeg 900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-profile-e1720031742525-297x141.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-profile-e1720031742525-120x57.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-profile-e1720031742525-768x364.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I think the coolest thing about Park Tool’s new BO-6 bottle opener is that it’s modeled after the iconic PW-4 pedal wrench, with two offset wrench openings. Pretty cool. But coolness factor aside, the mechanical advantage of the two different openings is obvious, and you get nice leverage from the long vinyl-dipped handle.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-again-e1720031049578.jpeg\"><img width=\"900\" height=\"667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-again-e1720031049578.jpeg\" alt=\"Park Tools Chain Breaker, Floor Pump and Bottle Opener BO-6 opening a bottle again\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-again-e1720031049578.jpeg 900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-again-e1720031049578-297x220.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-again-e1720031049578-120x89.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-again-e1720031049578-768x569.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-e1720031807565.jpeg\"><img width=\"900\" height=\"622\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-e1720031807565.jpeg\" alt=\"Park Tools Chain Breaker, Floor Pump and Bottle Opener BO-6 opening a bottle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-e1720031807565.jpeg 900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-e1720031807565-297x205.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-e1720031807565-120x83.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Park-Tools-Chain-Breaker-Floor-Pump-and-Bottle-Opener-BO-6-opening-a-bottle-e1720031807565-768x531.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This bad boy is made in the USA out of laser-cut stainless steel for a lifetime of use. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>BO-6 Retail and Features</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $35</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Compatible with glass bottles with pry-off caps, including: </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Beer</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Root Beer</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ginger Beer</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cider</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pop</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Kombucha</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sparkling Water and More! </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Get all of the bicycle-specific tools you need at the link below. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.parktool.com/en-us/\">ParkTool.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/park-tool-ct-15-chain-tool-bo-6-bottle-opener/\">Park Tool Rolls Out Professional Chain Tool, New Floor Pump &amp; Updated Bottle Opener</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"1f8c73124be3396561a4478add4481d4a7ededf19cf12c0dadc4c99830d7e01e","category":"Cycling"}